/ - "Root" the top of the file system hirearchy
/bin - Binary files are executable program, human readiable file
/etc - system configuration files, tell how the operating system behaves
/home - Home directories, seperate your data 
/opt - thrid party stored or optional
/tmp - temporary space, great place to store temp file
/usr - user related programs, 
/var - variable data, log file generated by application and os

Each directory can have their own set of sub directories

Top level directories
/boot - Files that are need to start or file used to boot the os 
/cgroup -  
/dev - 
/lib - 
/media - CD ROM USB 
/root - for root account
/srv - /srv/www
/srv/ftp

Applicatin Directory Structure
/usr/local/carashplan/bin
/usr/local/crashplan/etc
/usr/local/crashplan/lib
/usr/local/crashplan/log

/opt/avg/bin
/opt/avg/etc
/opt/avg/lib
/opt/avg/myapp
  

  
